**When to use**: Week 2–3. Designs auth flow, user roles, data isolation.

```
I need to design auth & multi-tenant isolation for VolunteerCalendar.org 
(Supabase).

User roles:
- Org Admin (full control, billing)
- Ministry Lead (can approve/tweak their ministry schedule only)
- Volunteer (view personal schedule, set blockouts, respond to requests)

Multi-tenant:
- Each church = org_id
- One admin can manage multiple churches
- Data strictly isolated (volunteer at Church A ≠ sees Church B)

Questions:
1. Design auth schema (users, orgs, role_members table).
2. Row-level security (RLS) policies in PostgreSQL:
   - Ministry Lead can only see volunteers/services in their ministry
   - Volunteer can only see their own assignments & household
   - Admin sees all within their org
3. Supabase Auth setup: email + Planning Center OAuth
4. Session management (refresh tokens, 2FA optional)
5. Audit log: Track who accessed/changed what

Return: Auth schema DDL, RLS policy pseudocode (PostgreSQL), 
Supabase Auth setup guide, data isolation diagram.
```

**Expected output**: Auth schema, RLS policies, Supabase setup steps. Implement week 2.

